Dirty Little Billy (1972 - USA)

Western
 
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0068487/


As the title indicates, the picture is an unvarnished study of gunslinger William Bonney, better known as Billy the Kid. Instead of the idealized outlaw seen in previous films, this version of the character is a deranged man-child with a homicidal streak. Clearly influenced by the darker, more sinister style of spaghetti westerns, the film offers a unique insight into the beginnings of the titular notorious outlaw. It marked Nick Nolte's film debut and was Jack L. Warner's last personal production.
